article.headline: Arkansas State 77, Austin Peay 70
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Arkansas State's Isaac Wells scored 23 points and brought down 12 rebounds to lead the Indians to a 77-70 win over Austin Peay on Saturday. Arkansas State (4-3) shot 56 percent from the field to come away with the win. The Indians also were helped by guard Adrian Banks' 21 points and four assists. The Indians held a 14-point lead at halftime and never trailed in the second half. Austin Peay managed to close the gap to 63-57 with 5:49 remaining, but the Governors came no closer. Austin Peay (0-3) remains winless on the season, despite forward Drake Reed's 31 points on Saturday. Fernandez Lockett also chipped in 10 points and 10 rebounds for the Governors.
